cs.CR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.HC 

This paper belongs to the field of cybersecurity (cs.CR) as it investigates the effects of language on cybercriminal activity. It also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it analyzes the language used in the emails. Additionally, it touches on the topic of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it studies how users interact with webmail accounts. The paper also involves the use of statistical analysis (cs.SI) to draw conclusions from the collected data. Finally, it relates to the field of cybercrime (cs.CY) as it investigates criminal activity in compromised webmail accounts.
